post_text:
We could really use a few extra helpers in the athletic booster club concession stand tonight for the last varsity home game.
The same folks end up helping us out every single week it seems, but it isn't feasible to expect them to be available every single Friday night.
The athletic booster club gave approximately $10,000 in scholarships to graduating Buna High School students last year, and with the help of our volunteers, we hope to do the same this year. There are so many students in our community that need help paying for college and this scholarship money can get them a good start.
Please consider joining the Buna Athletic Booster Club and helping the children in our community. Message me, comment, or text if you are interested in volunteering. (409) 489-8894 #GoCougars

post_text:
Everyone always ask why I do the booster club and usually I say because I love Buna. We put in long hours and listen to lots of complaining usually from the people who don't do anything. We volunteer and we don't always post everything but we try to get most of the stuff we attend. Several of us have thought about not coming back to the booster club because of all the negative comments and complaints. Well today I received a letter from a young man who was very thankful for receiving his booster club scholarship. Things like that make it all worth listening to all the negative stuff that comes along with dealing with the booster club. Brock Terry that scholarship was given to you because we know it will be put to good use as will the other 5 scholarships the booster club gave out this year. Being able to help out kids is why we do this. With that being said step up and help out the booster club this year and you will know how good it feels to help out a kid going on to the next chapter in their life. #Cougarnation
#GOBIGBLUE

post_text: Last night the Seniors presented Coach Terrier with a home plate signed by the 2015 Cougar Baseball team. Coach T you are probably wondering why it's an old crappy looking plate. I took that plate from the little league park 9 years ago when we replaced the ones at the ball park for allstars when the Seniors were 9 years old. They won the district Chamionship that year. We have used that plate some more over the years but that plate has had many of your former players step up to it. I figured this was a great time to use it and put it in it's final resting place. Thanks Coach T for a great season!
